h3. *Problem Statement*
It would be great if we could display the "Search" placeholder in Confluence.
Tested with Confluence 5.5 and above, the "Search" placeholder is no longer showing although when inspecting the element in browser, the "Search" placeholder is still clearly seen.

{code}
<input id="quick-search-query" class="text app-search search quick-search-query" type="text" accesskey="q" autocomplete="off" name="queryString" title="Quick Search (/or g , g)" placeholder="Search">
{code}

h3. *Current behaviour*
 !placeholder.PNG|thumbnail! 

h3. *Use Case*
When using the [documentation theme|https://confluence.atlassian.com/conf56/configuring-the-documentation-theme-658737059.html], it's possible to configure the search to limit the results to the specific space only. 

This would be extremely useful if Confluence is able to display this so that there's no confusion for the users.

However, it's understood that the *Documentation Theme will be obsolete starting from Confluence 6*.

h3. *Workaround*
# Apply a custom CSS to display the Search Placeholder.
(i) Note that customization is beyond [Atlassian's Support Offerings|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/Support/Atlassian+Support+Offerings]
# Go to Confluence Administration >> Custom HTML and edit the "At end of the HEAD"
# Add this code
{code}
<style type="text/css">
    #quick-search-query::-webkit-input-placeholder{
		color: #FFFFFF !important;
	}

    #quick-search-query::-moz-placeholder{
		color: #FFFFFF !important;
	}
</style>
{code}

h3. *Results after workaround*
 !search space.PNG|thumbnail!

